data.description: Live your 1920s fantasy after you polish this diamond in the rough. Built in 1925, this 3,360 sqft water view home in Seahurst sits on a huge 18000+ sq ft lot with gorgeous mature Japanese Maple and dogwood trees and multiple outdoor entertaining spaces. Many original details are still intact and add to the home’s character. Kitchens and baths upstairs and down offer more than enough space for guests or perhaps multigenerational living. This special place needs some love, but with your vision and the breathtaking views of the sound looking out to Vashon and the mountains, this one of a kind property has the potential to be amazing. Remodel it to make it your own or start from the ground up for your dream home. See it to believe it.
